1
00:00:13,972 --> 00:00:16,517
[GROUPIES cheering]

2
00:00:16,558 --> 00:00:17,351
You got this!

3
00:00:17,392 --> 00:00:18,393
‐‐Good luck, Joy!
‐‐[GROUPIE 08C] Yeah!

4
00:00:18,435 --> 00:00:20,312
Go out there and
show 'em who's boss!

5
00:00:20,354 --> 00:00:22,773
Ah, crap! Yu! Gimme some cover!

6
00:00:22,814 --> 00:00:23,649
[YUTA]
Uh‐‐

7
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:26,109
[KANAKO] I can't let them see
me, or they'll cause a scene.

8
00:00:26,151 --> 00:00:28,070
Hey, Maki!

9
00:00:28,111 --> 00:00:30,364
You better not lose your
first match, ya hear me?

10
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:32,574
Wait. Where did you
even come from?

11
00:00:32,616 --> 00:00:33,951
Do your best out there!

12
00:00:33,992 --> 00:00:35,702
You're gonna win
the whole tournament!

13
00:00:35,744 --> 00:00:37,829
Also, you look really hot!

14
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:40,290
Your fangirls are
crazier than usual.

15
00:00:40,332 --> 00:00:42,417
Thanks for comin' out
to watch my game, ladies!

16
00:00:42,459 --> 00:00:43,752
I'll win it just for you.

17
00:00:43,794 --> 00:00:45,712
Oh, my gosh, he waved at me!

18
00:00:45,754 --> 00:00:48,215
[BOTH screaming]

19
00:00:48,257 --> 00:00:50,050
Don't you think that's
a little over the top?

20
00:00:50,092 --> 00:00:52,469
Be careful, man.
They might hear you.

21
00:00:52,511 --> 00:00:54,012
Joy sure knows
how to handle them.

22
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:55,222
They eat it up.

23
00:00:55,264 --> 00:00:56,932
Guess he's used
to being popular.

24
00:00:56,974 --> 00:01:00,018
So? Do we have any
chance of beating him?

25
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:03,230
Maki and I looked through
the data together.

26
00:01:03,272 --> 00:01:06,942
We figured out their
preferred play style. But...

27
00:01:08,110 --> 00:01:09,695
This sure is exciting.

28
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:11,238
I can't wait to see it!

29
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:13,448
Those two are gonna
do great out there!

30
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:16,868
Oh, wow. You're
really into this!

31
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:19,830
I am. It's pretty fun, honestly!

32
00:01:19,871 --> 00:01:22,874
Not just the sport,
but being part of a club,

33
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:25,335
and cheering on your
teammates at games.

34
00:01:25,377 --> 00:01:27,296
I love every bit of it!

35
00:01:27,337 --> 00:01:30,048
[phone vibrating]

36
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:32,634
[gasps]

37
00:01:32,676 --> 00:01:34,303
Hey. What's up?

38
00:01:45,063 --> 00:01:46,523
Nao?

39
00:01:46,565 --> 00:01:49,568
I'm fine, and I'm different now.

40
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:52,279
It's okay! I've changed!

41
00:01:53,322 --> 00:01:56,742
[phone vibrating]

42
00:01:59,911 --> 00:02:08,295
[phone vibrating]

43
00:02:11,715 --> 00:02:12,841
[OFFICIAL 10C]
Serving side:

44
00:02:12,883 --> 00:02:16,720
Masami Ootomo and Joy
Kusakabe from Hatanooka.

45
00:02:16,762 --> 00:02:17,638
Receiving side:

46
00:02:17,679 --> 00:02:20,724
Toma Shinjo and Maki Katsuragi
from Shijo Minami.

47
00:02:20,766 --> 00:02:23,352
It's a five‐game
match. Play ball!

48
00:02:25,103 --> 00:02:29,191
Dang, he's tall. Might
as well be a wall.

49
00:02:29,232 --> 00:02:32,235
Come on. Focus. We got this!

50
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:49,670
There!

51
00:02:49,711 --> 00:02:53,131
[GROUPIES cheer]

52
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:54,883
Aw, yeah!

53
00:02:54,925 --> 00:02:57,552
Nothin' better than scorin'
a clean winner off a volley.

54
00:02:57,594 --> 00:02:59,388
It's my favorite
part of the game!

55
00:02:59,429 --> 00:03:01,765
Sure is an easy way to show off.

56
00:03:01,807 --> 00:03:02,808
Yeah, that, too.

57
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:05,852
That's the other
reason I like it.

58
00:03:05,894 --> 00:03:07,562
He could reach that shot.

59
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:10,524
Hey, don't worry.
Just keep this going.

60
00:03:10,565 --> 00:03:13,652
You got it. Let's have
some fun. Okay?

61
00:03:13,694 --> 00:03:15,779
Heh...

62
00:03:15,821 --> 00:03:17,155
[OFFICIAL 10C]
1‐0!

63
00:03:22,119 --> 00:03:23,537
‐‐[TOMA gasps]
‐‐[GROUPIES cheer]

64
00:03:23,578 --> 00:03:26,998
Whoa! There I go again! Nice!

65
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,875
What's with that guy?

66
00:03:28,917 --> 00:03:31,336
He's able to reach the ball
no matter where they hit it.

67
00:03:31,378 --> 00:03:33,130
How's that even possible?

68
00:03:33,171 --> 00:03:35,340
He's more of a monster
than we thought.

69
00:03:35,382 --> 00:03:36,633
Looks like it.

70
00:03:36,675 --> 00:03:39,511
I'll try scooting back a bit
and see what happens.

71
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:44,307
‐‐[TOMA gasps]
‐‐[GROUPIES cheer]

72
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:48,687
Oh, wow, sometimes
I am just too good.

73
00:03:48,729 --> 00:03:49,896
Well, damn.

74
00:03:49,938 --> 00:03:52,899
That serve was so fast,
I could barely see it.

75
00:03:59,364 --> 00:04:02,159
You can try, but
you're still no match.

76
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:04,202
[OFFICIAL 10C]
Game! Change sides!

77
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:05,662
Joy! You're the coolest!

78
00:04:05,704 --> 00:04:07,038
That was amazing!

79
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,415
Give us a wave!

80
00:04:08,457 --> 00:04:10,041
Hey, let's finish
this match up quickly

81
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:11,251
so I can go grab a smoothie.

82
00:04:11,293 --> 00:04:12,836
Seriously?

83
00:04:13,837 --> 00:04:15,380
[TOMA]
If Joy's first serve stays in,

84
00:04:15,422 --> 00:04:17,090
there's not much we can do.

85
00:04:17,132 --> 00:04:18,633
I'm not so sure about that.

86
00:04:18,675 --> 00:04:20,051
Oh, yeah?

87
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:21,928
We can't run from him forever.

88
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:22,804
[GROUPIES cheering]

89
00:04:22,846 --> 00:04:25,265
[TOMA] You wanna try to
return that monster's shots?

90
00:04:25,307 --> 00:04:27,184
[MAKI]
What? Is that too reckless?

91
00:04:27,225 --> 00:04:28,518
Of course it is.

92
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:31,396
Remember, this is soft
tennis that we're playing.

93
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:32,522
Right.

94
00:04:32,564 --> 00:04:35,066
[OFFICIAL 10C]
Game score. 0‐1!

95
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:36,651
[TOMA]
He makes a good point.

96
00:04:36,693 --> 00:04:38,236
It's like Ryoma always said.

97
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:41,364
Strength alone doesn't
win a match in soft tennis!

98
00:04:46,369 --> 00:04:47,454
[gasps]

99
00:04:49,247 --> 00:04:50,540
[TOMA]
He's gigantic!

100
00:04:50,582 --> 00:04:52,918
Ha!

101
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:54,044
Aw, not again!

102
00:04:54,085 --> 00:04:56,254
He just volleys it
back every time!

103
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:57,964
This game isn't fair at all.

104
00:04:58,006 --> 00:05:00,967
How are we supposed to win?

105
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:02,928
I believe in the two of them.

106
00:05:02,969 --> 00:05:04,262
[TOMA]
Damn it!

107
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:05,222
Take it easy.

108
00:05:05,263 --> 00:05:06,890
And just wait to lose?

109
00:05:06,932 --> 00:05:09,643
Let's try not to worry about
winning or losing right now.

110
00:05:09,684 --> 00:05:11,353
We're playing tennis!

111
00:05:13,688 --> 00:05:16,608
[TOMA'S MOM]
It's impossible for you.

112
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:19,486
You'll never be
anything like Ryoma.

113
00:05:25,116 --> 00:05:28,036
Hey. Remember our
match against Arashi.

114
00:05:28,078 --> 00:05:28,870
[TOMA]
What?

115
00:05:28,912 --> 00:05:30,664
[MAKI] Joy uses his height
to his advantage and defends

116
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:32,833
a huge area, but if
you think about it,

117
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:35,460
couldn't that turn into
a weakness in doubles?

118
00:05:37,212 --> 00:05:39,172
He's not the only
one on the court.

119
00:05:39,214 --> 00:05:41,424
And we'll use that against them.

120
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:49,766
Whoa! Toma used his cut serve!

121
00:06:12,539 --> 00:06:13,540
There!

122
00:06:16,293 --> 00:06:17,377
We did it!

123
00:06:17,419 --> 00:06:18,545
We got a point.

124
00:06:18,587 --> 00:06:20,255
Wow, that was incredible!

125
00:06:20,297 --> 00:06:21,590
Yeah, they lucked out!

126
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:22,424
No way.

127
00:06:22,465 --> 00:06:23,717
[ITSUKI
Huh?

128
00:06:23,758 --> 00:06:25,969
Pretty sure those two
must have figured out

129
00:06:26,011 --> 00:06:27,429
a way to beat Joy.

130
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:29,139
Should we keep trying that?

131
00:06:29,180 --> 00:06:31,308
Yeah, sure. Keep it up.

132
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:32,559
[OFFICIAL 10C]
One all!

133
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:37,063
[OOTOMO]
Him, too?

134
00:07:00,086 --> 00:07:01,129
But why?

135
00:07:01,171 --> 00:07:02,714
[GROUP cheers]

136
00:07:02,756 --> 00:07:05,050
‐‐[TSUBASA] Way to make a play!
‐‐[ARASHI] Well. Not bad

137
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:07,677
Come on! Joy didn't get to hit
the ball that whole point!

138
00:07:07,719 --> 00:07:08,553
That's so lame.

139
00:07:08,595 --> 00:07:11,473
I wanna see Joy do all those
cool moves and stuff!

140
00:07:15,894 --> 00:07:17,062
This one's mine!

141
00:07:19,397 --> 00:07:20,565
[JOY]
Again?

142
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:35,747
[OFFICIAL 10C]
Out!

143
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:37,540
[GROUP cheers]

144
00:07:37,582 --> 00:07:39,793
Good job

145
00:07:39,834 --> 00:07:41,461
But how?

146
00:07:42,754 --> 00:07:44,798
[OFFICIAL 10C]
Game score: one all!

147
00:07:55,767 --> 00:07:57,435
What the heck is going on?

148
00:08:05,694 --> 00:08:07,028
‐‐[OFFICIAL 10C] Game!
‐‐[SHINGO] Whoa!

149
00:08:07,070 --> 00:08:08,321
Yeah! They're on a roll!

150
00:08:08,363 --> 00:08:09,155
Another one!

151
00:08:09,197 --> 00:08:10,615
That's so awesome!

152
00:08:10,657 --> 00:08:11,992
Well done.

153
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:13,785
Good! Yes, yes!

154
00:08:13,827 --> 00:08:14,869
[OFFICIAL 10C]
Change sides!

155
00:08:14,911 --> 00:08:17,872
I don't know what's happening,
but I don't like it.

156
00:08:19,416 --> 00:08:20,625
Let's finish them off.

157
00:08:20,667 --> 00:08:22,085
Sounds good.

158
00:08:22,127 --> 00:08:24,087
[OFFICIAL 10C]
Game score: 2‐1!

159
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:35,974
[JOY]
He's dead weight.

160
00:08:36,016 --> 00:08:37,308
Oh, yeah!

161
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:38,727
They've got momentum.

162
00:08:38,768 --> 00:08:40,520
If they lose now,
they're idiots.

163
00:08:40,562 --> 00:08:42,105
You're so full of yourself.

164
00:08:42,147 --> 00:08:43,356
Of course I am.

165
00:08:43,398 --> 00:08:46,109
'Cause I'm totally awesome!

166
00:08:46,151 --> 00:08:47,318
1‐0!

167
00:09:03,376 --> 00:09:04,836
[NAO]
Yeah!

168
00:09:04,878 --> 00:09:06,337
Don't tell me he's gonna lose!

169
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:07,881
How could that even happen?

170
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:10,008
This doesn't make any sense!

171
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:13,178
Hey, look, guys, that's
Joy from Hatanooka, isn't it?

172
00:09:13,219 --> 00:09:16,222
There's no way! Is he
losing in the first round?

173
00:09:16,264 --> 00:09:18,767
Who's he playing?

174
00:09:18,808 --> 00:09:20,810
Is that Shijo Minami?

175
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:23,938
This again?

176
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:30,028
[OFFICIAL 10C]
Out!

177
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:31,196
All right!

178
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:32,697
Take 'em down, you guys!

179
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:36,493
One more point! We only
need one more point!

180
00:09:39,412 --> 00:09:42,165
Y'know. Ryoma approved
of you joining the club

181
00:09:42,207 --> 00:09:45,710
and even thought
you'd do well. Huh?

182
00:09:45,752 --> 00:09:48,713
I'll join the club.
But only if you pay me.

183
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:49,839
Uh‐‐

184
00:09:49,881 --> 00:09:52,467
Aw, what's the matter?
I'm not made of free time.

185
00:09:52,509 --> 00:09:55,553
But paid time, is something
that I can get behind.

186
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:57,889
I'll charge you
for manual labor.

187
00:10:00,809 --> 00:10:01,851
Okay!

188
00:10:01,893 --> 00:10:03,353
C'mon, Maki!

189
00:10:03,394 --> 00:10:04,646
Give it up, Katsuragi.

190
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:07,273
I'm not gonna stop
till I'm done.

191
00:10:07,315 --> 00:10:09,818
This is it. The last lap!

192
00:10:18,118 --> 00:10:20,328
[TOMA, MAKI]
Finish!

193
00:10:20,370 --> 00:10:21,955
You and me can win.

194
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:23,957
Will you pair up with me?

195
00:10:27,544 --> 00:10:30,088
[MAKI]
Hey.

196
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:32,465
I'm ready, I wanna do this.

197
00:10:32,507 --> 00:10:35,135
Me, too. Thanks, Maki.

198
00:10:39,347 --> 00:10:41,683
[GROUP]
Maki! Maki!

199
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:44,227
[RINTARO]
Okay, guys. We did it.

200
00:10:44,269 --> 00:10:46,521
Now let's welcome our
newest member to the team.

201
00:10:46,563 --> 00:10:49,691
Come on. Bring it
in for Katsuragi.

202
00:10:53,069 --> 00:10:57,866
[GROUP]
Maki! Maki! Maki! Maki! Maki!

203
00:10:57,907 --> 00:11:00,326
I have eyes, you know!

204
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:01,911
Looks like you're havin'
fun in the front.

205
00:11:01,953 --> 00:11:03,454
You smug jerk.

206
00:11:05,248 --> 00:11:07,000
[TSUBASA]
Dirty little!

207
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:08,293
[yells]

208
00:11:10,295 --> 00:11:11,421
Tsubasa!

209
00:11:20,513 --> 00:11:21,514
On it!

210
00:11:33,401 --> 00:11:37,363
[GROUP]
Maki! Maki! Maki! Maki!

211
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:42,744
Maki! Maki! Maki! Maki!

212
00:11:42,785 --> 00:11:44,120
[OFFICIAL 10C]
3‐0!

213
00:11:44,162 --> 00:11:47,081
I'm gonna give this one
everything I've got.

214
00:11:51,085 --> 00:11:52,253
[gasps]

215
00:11:56,174 --> 00:11:57,342
[MAKI grunts]

216
00:12:02,847 --> 00:12:04,849
[yells]

217
00:12:12,774 --> 00:12:14,317
You aced him.

218
00:12:14,359 --> 00:12:16,027
[MAKI]
Yeah. I did.

219
00:12:17,487 --> 00:12:18,529
[OFFICIAL 10C]
Game, set.

220
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:20,490
With a game score of 3‐1.

221
00:12:20,531 --> 00:12:23,493
Shijo Minami's Shinjo
and Katsuragi pair wins!

222
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:24,869
Yes! They actually did it!

223
00:12:24,911 --> 00:12:26,621
[YUTA]
They won! They really won!

224
00:12:26,663 --> 00:12:27,497
Hell yeah!

225
00:12:27,538 --> 00:12:29,749
Yes! Yes! Yes! I knew
they could do it!

226
00:12:29,791 --> 00:12:31,209
I never doubted them
for a second!

227
00:12:31,251 --> 00:12:32,627
We won! We won!

228
00:12:32,669 --> 00:12:34,671
We sure did! We beat them!

229
00:12:34,712 --> 00:12:36,339
Those two were actually
able to pull out

230
00:12:36,381 --> 00:12:38,549
a pretty convincing win.

231
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:40,176
[RINTARO]
Toma and Maki are amazing!

232
00:12:40,218 --> 00:12:42,136
They're a good pair.

233
00:12:42,178 --> 00:12:46,307
They were able to win.
I can't believe it!

234
00:12:46,349 --> 00:12:48,559
[RINTARO]
That was so cool!

235
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:49,978
[ITSUKI]
Did you see that serve?

236
00:12:50,019 --> 00:12:51,562
It was incredible!

237
00:12:52,981 --> 00:12:54,065
Good game.

238
00:12:54,107 --> 00:12:55,525
You, too.

239
00:12:55,566 --> 00:12:57,151
We won.

240
00:12:58,403 --> 00:12:59,821
We won.

241
00:13:02,991 --> 00:13:06,160
Thank you, Maki.

242
00:13:06,202 --> 00:13:08,788
[MAKI]
Mm‐hm.

243
00:13:08,830 --> 00:13:14,294
[SOFT TENNIS CLUB cheering]

244
00:13:14,335 --> 00:13:16,921
Y'know, I'm starting
to think I'm not cut out

245
00:13:16,963 --> 00:13:18,923
for soft tennis after all.

246
00:13:18,965 --> 00:13:21,551
I think we've done
pretty well so far!

247
00:13:21,592 --> 00:13:23,177
[JOY] Maybe I'll just quit
this stupid sport.

248
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:26,472
Hey, wait, are you serious?

249
00:13:26,514 --> 00:13:28,266
Oh, wait, I've got it!

250
00:13:28,308 --> 00:13:30,476
I think I'll join
a tennis table club!

251
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,603
Yeah, that sounds cool, right?

252
00:13:37,692 --> 00:13:41,863
[phone vibrating]

253
00:13:41,904 --> 00:13:43,990
[VOICEMAIL 11A] Your call has
been sent to voice mail.

254
00:13:44,032 --> 00:13:46,451
Please record a message
after the beep.

255
00:13:57,545 --> 00:13:58,838
I don't get it.

256
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:02,759
I don't understand why you're
always being so selfish.

257
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:05,386
Everything I ever do
is for your own good.

258
00:14:05,428 --> 00:14:08,014
But why can't you even see that?

259
00:14:08,056 --> 00:14:11,017
It's only because I care.

260
00:14:11,059 --> 00:14:15,063
It's okay. I'll let
this slide for today.

261
00:14:15,104 --> 00:14:18,983
But don't forget, you will
always be my child.

262
00:14:19,025 --> 00:14:21,361
No matter what happens,
you are mine.

263
00:14:21,402 --> 00:14:23,613
You're my boy.

264
00:14:23,654 --> 00:14:26,866
This is all for
your own sake. Nao.

265
00:14:29,744 --> 00:14:31,913
I can't believe
Hatanooka's Kusakabe's

266
00:14:31,954 --> 00:14:33,081
out in the first round!

267
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:34,332
Joy really lost?

268
00:14:34,374 --> 00:14:35,375
Who are those guys?

269
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:37,043
Hey, I got some info!

270
00:14:37,085 --> 00:14:39,253
I hear it's Shijo Minami's
second‐year pair,

271
00:14:39,295 --> 00:14:41,089
Shinjo and Katsuragi.

272
00:14:41,130 --> 00:14:41,923
Really?

273
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:44,092
[PLAYER 11F] I've never
heard of those two before!

274
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:45,259
[PLAYER 11E]
It's prob'ly just a fluke!

275
00:14:45,301 --> 00:14:48,554
[SORA]
Shinjo...

276
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:50,473
How interesting.

277
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:03,611
[SORA] Joy Kusakabe's pair
lost to Shijo Minami.

278
00:15:03,653 --> 00:15:04,737
[gasps]

279
00:15:04,779 --> 00:15:08,658
It's those two guys we saw
over at the shrine with Arashi.

280
00:15:08,699 --> 00:15:12,370
Turns out, one of them is
Ryoma Shinjo's little brother.

281
00:15:12,412 --> 00:15:16,416
I see. So, if they were
able to beat Joy...

282
00:15:16,457 --> 00:15:18,042
We could meet.

283
00:15:19,877 --> 00:15:21,379
Well done, everyone!

284
00:15:21,421 --> 00:15:24,132
You might've lost, but
those were good matches!

285
00:15:24,173 --> 00:15:27,301
And our Shinjo Katsuragi
pair pulled off a victory!

286
00:15:27,343 --> 00:15:28,928
Our first win!

287
00:15:28,970 --> 00:15:30,972
Give 'em a round of applause!

288
00:15:33,683 --> 00:15:36,644
What's gives? That was
some weak clapping.

289
00:15:36,686 --> 00:15:38,396
We cheered our
asses off earlier,

290
00:15:38,438 --> 00:15:39,689
so we're just tired of it.

291
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:41,190
Yeah, we sure did.

292
00:15:41,232 --> 00:15:42,900
That aside, what's next?

293
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:44,068
Who are they going to play?

294
00:15:44,110 --> 00:15:45,153
That's a good point!

295
00:15:45,194 --> 00:15:46,571
It's more important
to know that!

296
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:48,406
Yeah, all right, slow down.

297
00:15:48,448 --> 00:15:49,991
'Kay, let's see, up next.

298
00:15:50,032 --> 00:15:51,909
Would you hurry it up already?

299
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:56,581
We're facing Ooinishi Middle
School's third‐year pair?

300
00:15:56,622 --> 00:15:58,583
Why does it always have
to be third years?

301
00:15:58,624 --> 00:16:00,710
Can't they give us
a little break?

302
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:02,920
Try throwing some
first years at us.

303
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:04,672
I'm with you there.

304
00:16:04,714 --> 00:16:07,008
Well, I think we stand a chance.

305
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:10,511
[OFFICIAL 11A]
Serving side:

306
00:16:10,553 --> 00:16:13,347
Shinjo and Katsuragi
from Shijo Minami.

307
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:14,432
Receiving side:

308
00:16:14,474 --> 00:16:16,809
Sakai and Yamashita
from Ooinishi.

309
00:16:16,851 --> 00:16:19,437
It's a five‐game
match. Play ball!

310
00:16:24,358 --> 00:16:25,735
[GROUP cheering]

311
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:26,611
Nice volley.

312
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:28,154
Thanks, Nice serve.

313
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:39,957
[OFFICIAL 11A]
Game, set.

314
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:42,043
With a game score of 3‐0,

315
00:16:42,084 --> 00:16:44,587
Shinjo and Katsuragi
from Shijo Minami win!

316
00:16:44,629 --> 00:16:46,172
[PLAYER 11F]
That's a straight set.

317
00:16:46,214 --> 00:16:47,673
[PLAYER 11H]
But Sakai and Yamashita made it

318
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:49,342
to the top eight last year!

319
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:51,886
[PLAYER 11G] Just how far
are those two gonna go?

320
00:16:51,928 --> 00:16:53,179
[ALL cheering]

321
00:16:53,221 --> 00:16:54,972
So good! Too good!

322
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:56,682
They got a straight
set off of 'em!

323
00:16:56,724 --> 00:16:57,808
Yeah, big whoop.

324
00:16:57,850 --> 00:16:59,560
Those guys were
a buncha pushovers.

325
00:16:59,602 --> 00:17:02,480
I don't really
think that's true.

326
00:17:02,522 --> 00:17:04,857
Hang on. Where'd Arashi go?

327
00:17:04,899 --> 00:17:06,609
He went to play his match.

328
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:18,496
[ARASHI yells]

329
00:17:18,538 --> 00:17:20,248
[PLAYER 11J grunts]

330
00:17:20,289 --> 00:17:21,290
That was mine.

331
00:17:21,332 --> 00:17:23,376
I can't believe how
much you guys suck!

332
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:25,086
Oji, please try to refrain from

333
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:27,046
loudly taunting your
opponent like that.

334
00:17:27,088 --> 00:17:27,880
It's bad manners.

335
00:17:27,922 --> 00:17:30,007
I'm just talkin' to myself!

336
00:17:32,969 --> 00:17:34,220
[SHINGO]
Hey, check it out!

337
00:17:34,262 --> 00:17:35,346
We're on our third match!

338
00:17:35,388 --> 00:17:37,723
Who would've thought that
we'd make it this far?

339
00:17:37,765 --> 00:17:39,475
These games are
making me nervous!

340
00:17:39,517 --> 00:17:41,727
It's a good thing we're
not playing, right?

341
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:43,813
So, we all gotta cheer 'em on!

342
00:17:43,854 --> 00:17:45,189
Let's show our support!

343
00:17:45,231 --> 00:17:46,732
[SOFT TENNIS CLUB]
Let's go, let's go, let's go,

344
00:17:46,774 --> 00:17:48,109
let's go, let's go Shijo!

345
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:49,694
Let's win, let's win,
let's win...

346
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:51,529
This is so cool.

347
00:17:51,571 --> 00:17:52,530
[OFFICIAL 11C]
Serving side:

348
00:17:52,572 --> 00:17:55,116
Kimura and Nakatani
from Umagomekita.

349
00:17:55,157 --> 00:17:55,950
Receiving side:

350
00:17:55,992 --> 00:17:58,244
Shijo Minami's Shinjo
and Katsuragi.

351
00:17:58,286 --> 00:18:00,705
It's a five‐game
match. Play ball!

352
00:18:05,126 --> 00:18:06,168
[gasps]

353
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:07,795
Nice, they scored!

354
00:18:07,837 --> 00:18:10,256
It seems like they've totally
hit their stride now.

355
00:18:16,429 --> 00:18:17,471
[OFFICIAL 11C]
Game, set!

356
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:18,889
With a game score of 3‐1,

357
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:22,351
Shijo Minami's Shinjo
and Katsuragi pair wins!

358
00:18:22,393 --> 00:18:23,561
Another win!

359
00:18:23,603 --> 00:18:26,439
[SOFT TENNIS CLUB cheers]

360
00:18:27,898 --> 00:18:30,109
[SOFT TENNIS CLUB] Whoa!
Go, go, go, go, go, go, go, go!

361
00:18:30,151 --> 00:18:32,028
[TAKAYUKI]
They've gotten so strong.

362
00:18:32,069 --> 00:18:35,990
Maybe we could've gone far
in the team tournament.

363
00:18:36,032 --> 00:18:37,325
[SPECTATOR 11A]
Look, those guys are facing

364
00:18:37,366 --> 00:18:38,576
the Itsuse brothers next.

365
00:18:38,618 --> 00:18:41,412
[SPECTATOR 11B] Ah man, that's
too bad. It's over for them.

366
00:18:41,454 --> 00:18:42,705
[SPECTATOR 11C]
There's absolutely no way

367
00:18:42,747 --> 00:18:44,582
they're gonna beat those twins.

368
00:18:44,624 --> 00:18:46,208
[SPECTATOR 11D] They're last
year's national champions

369
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:47,960
after all.

370
00:18:48,002 --> 00:18:50,463
Those two are the champions?

371
00:18:51,631 --> 00:18:54,342
Tsubasa seems more nervous
than anyone else here.

372
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:56,677
They're pretty
intimidating. Makes sense.

373
00:18:56,719 --> 00:18:57,928
They look strong.

374
00:18:57,970 --> 00:18:59,847
And experienced.

375
00:18:59,889 --> 00:19:01,182
They're all good looking.

376
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:04,852
Arashi, Joy, now these twins.
That pisses me off.

377
00:19:04,894 --> 00:19:06,270
[phone vibrating]

378
00:19:06,312 --> 00:19:07,647
Huh?

379
00:19:13,527 --> 00:19:14,695
[RINTARO gasps]

380
00:19:17,782 --> 00:19:19,158
[RINTARO'S BIRTH MOTHER]
I took the liberty of watching

381
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,744
your soft tennis match today.

382
00:19:21,786 --> 00:19:26,290
It was a very good effort
and I'm proud of you.

383
00:19:26,332 --> 00:19:31,879
It's such a shame that you lost,
but I'm going home for today.

384
00:19:31,921 --> 00:19:37,635
I hope we can talk someday.
Please take care, Rintaro.

385
00:19:37,677 --> 00:19:39,220
Hey, what's up, man?

386
00:19:39,261 --> 00:19:41,806
[RINTARO'S BIRTH MOTHER]
From, your mother.

387
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:43,933
Do you mind if I write that?

388
00:19:43,974 --> 00:19:45,643
[ITSUKI]
You okay?

389
00:19:47,603 --> 00:19:49,313
Mom!

390
00:19:49,355 --> 00:19:50,648
Rintaro!

391
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:13,045
Let's all have a good match.

392
00:20:13,087 --> 00:20:14,797
Let's all have a good match.

393
00:20:14,839 --> 00:20:16,424
Same to you.

394
00:20:16,465 --> 00:20:18,467
Same to you.

395
00:20:18,509 --> 00:20:19,385
[OFFICIAL 11D]
Serving side:

396
00:20:19,427 --> 00:20:22,263
Shiratori's Riku Itsuse
and Sora Itsuse pair.

397
00:20:22,304 --> 00:20:24,765
Versus receiving side:
Shijo Minami's

398
00:20:24,807 --> 00:20:27,309
Toma Shinjo and
Maki Katsuragi pair.

399
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:30,396
It's a five‐game
match. Play ball!

400
00:20:38,446 --> 00:20:40,197
[gasps]

401
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:41,365
What was that?

402
00:20:41,407 --> 00:20:43,242
I couldn't even see
it. That's fast.

403
00:20:43,284 --> 00:20:44,744
It went by so quickly,

404
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:46,871
and I think I even
saw it curve, too.

405
00:20:46,912 --> 00:20:49,165
It has the same speed
as Joy's serve,

406
00:20:49,206 --> 00:20:51,625
and he added a slice
to top it off.

407
00:20:58,549 --> 00:20:59,592
[gasps]

408
00:21:07,266 --> 00:21:09,268
[TOMA grunts]

409
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:10,644
[OFFICIAL 11D]
Out!

410
00:21:16,192 --> 00:21:18,527
[OFFICIAL 11D]
Game! Change sides!

411
00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:23,032
So good!

412
00:21:23,073 --> 00:21:26,076
Hard to believe that you had
even more fried noodles!

413
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:29,663
Plus, this one's got bitter
melon and Spam inside!

414
00:21:29,705 --> 00:21:31,999
Maki, you are the greatest!

415
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:34,251
Think so?

416
00:21:34,293 --> 00:21:37,004
In that case, can you
tell me something?

417
00:21:37,046 --> 00:21:39,715
[ARASHI]
Hm? Yeah, sure. What?

418
00:21:39,757 --> 00:21:40,841
[MAKI]
Tell me what you know about

419
00:21:40,883 --> 00:21:42,551
the next pair we're facing.

420
00:21:42,593 --> 00:21:44,720
[ARASHI] 'Kay, just lemme
know who they are.

421
00:21:44,762 --> 00:21:46,180
The Itsuses.

422
00:21:47,765 --> 00:21:50,309
Do you know a good way
we can beat them?

423
00:21:50,351 --> 00:21:53,521
Are there any tricks
or strategies?

424
00:21:53,562 --> 00:21:56,649
[ARASHI] You wanna beat
the Itsuse brothers?

425
00:21:56,690 --> 00:21:59,151
[MAKI gasps]

426
00:21:59,193 --> 00:22:02,780
[ARASHI] Don't you dare
take soft tennis lightly.

427
00:22:02,822 --> 00:22:05,241
It'd be easier to just let
you know your chances

428
00:22:05,282 --> 00:22:08,702
of beating them at
your experience level.

429
00:22:08,744 --> 00:22:11,121
And that's zero percent!

430
00:22:13,707 --> 00:22:18,420
These guys're really
good. Too good.

431
00:23:43,714 --> 00:23:45,466
[TOMA'S MOM] It's taken
a long time to realize

432
00:23:45,507 --> 00:23:46,926
my true feelings,

433
00:23:46,967 --> 00:23:49,720
and I've given him
some painful memories.

434
00:23:49,762 --> 00:23:51,722
But it's for the best.

435
00:23:51,764 --> 00:23:53,599
If that's really
what you wanna do,

436
00:23:53,641 --> 00:23:55,976
then you should do it.

437
00:23:56,018 --> 00:24:01,690
Thank you, Ryoma.
I truly appreciate it.

438
00:24:01,732 --> 00:24:03,150
I want you to know
that those two

439
00:24:03,192 --> 00:24:08,572
are precious to me,
so I'll protect them

440
00:24:08,614 --> 00:24:14,828
by whatever means necessary.
I promise you that.

